<title>JAPAN: Japan trade watchdog raids NTT's cell phone unit.</title>
<headline>Japan trade watchdog raids NTT's cell phone unit.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp's cellular phone unit said the Fair Trade Commission raided its Tokyo office on Thursday morning because of allegations of price-fixing on its cellular phone handsets.</p>
<p>Two other cellular phone operators, Tokyo Digital Phone Co and Tu-Ka Cellular Tokyo Inc, also confirmed that the FTC, Japan's anti-monopoly watchdog, raided their offices.</p>
<p>&quot;The FTC investigated the office on allegations there have been violations of the anti-monopoly law,&quot; a spokesman at NTT Mobile Communications Network Inc said.</p>
<p>The handsets are sold by sales agents and not by the companies.</p>
<p>The FTC declined to comment.</p>
